<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Dirty Tricks: Ideas for enhancing this ability are flying around and I'm liking that. So far:<br>
-Nearsight<br>
-Stacking Self Haste while DT is active<br>
-Reduction in style endurance cost while DT is active<br>
-Acuity stat debuff<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A merc left alone on a caster should already kill that caster. They are already calling for determination nerfs. I don't want anything that will further debilitate casters specifically. I think it would be unfair and overpowering.<br>
I'd like something that makes us have a little more offense added during the effect. That is why I like the stacking haste or the endurance cost reduction better. Similar to TW and getting a stacking DA and no crits I'd like to see Dirt take on that same two fold ability. Improve defense by causing fumbles and increase offense with the end cost reduction, haste, or something to that effect. Perhaps even some bump to weaponskill during the 30 seconds could provide the needed double edge. <p>Thanks,<br>
<br>
